 projects render visible the often-hidden innovation within contemporary architecture. Five different construction methods are documented using photographs and isometric analytical drawings of building shells at a scale of 1:15. This book is intended to stimulate a profound discussion of future developments. Detailed insight into construction methods using the example of contemporary Swiss architecture Isometric detail drawings and a unique photo essay Buildings by EMI, Caruso St John, Peter Märkli, Meier Hug, Esch Sintzel, and many more  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aArchitecturezSwitzerland. 0aBuildingszSwitzerland. 4aKonstruktion. 4aMaterialoptimierung. 4aNachhaltigkeit. 4aSchweizer Architektur. 4aeffizient bauen. 4azeitgenössische Architektur.  aCaruso St John.  aEMI.  aEsch Sintzel.  aMeier Hug.  aPeter Märkli.  aconstruction method.  aconstruction.  acontemporary architecture.  agreen architecture.  anew technical possibility.  asustainability demand.  asustainability.  asustainable architecture.  asustainable building.1 aAmstutz, Joël, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBajovic, Natalija, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarroso, Leandro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerberat, Céline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBracher, Kevin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFischer, Romano, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGötschi, Lea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHauser, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeeb, Meret, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocab